  "text": ". WB was performed as previously described by us [CITATION_1] . Briefly, cell lysates were prepared by homogenization in RIPA buffer (150 mM sodium chloride, 50 mM Tris-HCl, pH 7.4, 1 mM ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid, 1 mM phenylmethylsulfonyl flouride, 1% Triton X-100, 1% sodium deoxycholic acid, 0.1% sodium dodecylsulfate) containing 5 µg/ml of aprotinin, and 5 µg/ml of leupeptin. Cell debris was removed by centrifugation. Protein concentration was determined with the Bio-Rad protein assay. Cell lysates were boiled for 5 min in 1X SDS sample buffer (50 mM Tris-HCl pH 6.8, 12.5% glycerol, 1% sodium dodecylsulfate, 0.01% bromophenol blue) containing 5% β-mercaptoethanol. Adrenal cell lysate (positive control for MC2R) was obtained from VWR.",
